The paper deals with machine learning models for streamflow prediction, which falls under the broad category of data science and machine learning. The use of decision trees and LSTMs also suggests a focus on machine learning techniques, which is why cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with the issue of limited training data, which is a common problem in data science, and could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DS and cs.CE. Finally, the use of neural networks in the study suggests a possible connection to the sub-category of cs.NE.
